lines.text: Calcium: leaf 120 mg and flower bud 65 mg
Potassium: leaf 690 mg and flower bud 500 mg
Vitamin C: leaf 40,8 mg and flower bud 23.3 mg
Fibre: leaf 7.7 g and flower bud 8.2 g
Protein: leaf 3.1 g and flower bud 3.5 g
The dandelion, known as a weed, it is a versatile
food plant. Young leaves, buds, flowers and roots are
all suitable for eating. The leaves are at their best in
early summer and can be used in the same way as
lettuce or herbs. The roots can also be used in many
ways: roasted roots can be used to make a hot drink
